---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import SiteFooter from '../components/SiteFooter.astro';
import SiteHeader from '../components/SiteHeader.astro';
---

<Base
  title="About AfterWage — The Real Hourly Wage Calculator"
  description="A free, no-signup true hourly wage calculator based on the Your Money or Your Life concept. Find out what you can really afford on your salary after the full cost of working."
  keywords="your money or your life calculator, real hourly wage tool, free wage calculator no signup"
>
  <SiteHeader theme="light" />

  <main class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-6 pt-28 pb-16 md:pt-32 md:pb-24">
    <a href="/" class="block font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-mute hover:text-blood">
      &larr; Back to the calculator
    </a>

    <h1 class="font-display font-light text-5xl md:text-6xl tracking-tightest mt-8 mb-6">
      About
    </h1>

    <p class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-mute mb-10">
      Last updated: April 20, 2026
    </p>

    <div class="space-y-6 font-body text-lg leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        This is a single-purpose calculator that asks a simple question: when
        you subtract everything your job actually costs you, and divide by
        every hour it actually takes, what's your real hourly wage?
      </p>

      <p>
        The answer is almost always smaller than the number on your offer
        letter. Sometimes a lot smaller.
      </p>

      <p>
        The concept comes from the 1992 book <a href="https://vickirobin.com/your-money-or-your-life/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="underline decoration-blood decoration-2 underline-offset-4 hover:text-blood"><em>Your Money or Your Life</em></a>
        by Vicki Robin and Joe Dominguez. The math has been around for
        thirty years. The internet has been surprisingly bad at putting it
        into a tool that loads fast, doesn't ask for your email, and lets
        you type in what you're about to buy to see what it actually costs
        you in time.
      </p>

      <p>
        That's what this is. The full math is on the <a href="/methodology" class="underline decoration-blood decoration-2 underline-offset-4 hover:text-blood">methodology page</a>
        if you want to see exactly how the numbers are produced.
      </p>

      <div class="pt-8 border-t border-ink/10 mt-12">
        <h2 class="font-display font-light text-2xl tracking-tightest mb-4">
          No, seriously, no signup
        </h2>
        <p>
          Every calculation runs in your browser. We don't store your
          numbers, send them anywhere, or try to upsell you on a
          subscription. The full data-handling story is in the
          <a href="/privacy" class="underline decoration-blood decoration-2 underline-offset-4 hover:text-blood">privacy policy</a>
          if you want the boring version.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="pt-8 border-t border-ink/10 mt-12">
        <h2 class="font-display font-light text-2xl tracking-tightest mb-4">Contact</h2>
        <p>
          Corrections, complaints, or calculator ideas go through the
          <a
            href="/contact"
            class="underline decoration-blood decoration-2 underline-offset-4 hover:text-blood"
          >
            contact form
          </a>
          . No email address on this site, because spam bots.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="pt-10 border-t border-ink/10 mt-12">
        <h2 class="font-display font-light text-2xl tracking-tightest mb-6">Related</h2>
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-base">
          <li>
            <a href="/" class="font-display text-xl underline decoration-blood decoration-2 underline-offset-4 hover:text-blood">Run the calculator</a>
            <span class="text-mute"> &mdash; back to AfterWage to find your real hourly wage.</span>
          </li>
          <li>
            <a href="/methodology" class="font-display text-xl underline decoration-blood decoration-2 underline-offset-4 hover:text-blood">Methodology</a>
            <span class="text-mute"> &mdash; the full math, the sources, and what's deliberately left out.</span>
          </li>
          <li>
            <a href="/contact" class="font-display text-xl underline decoration-blood decoration-2 underline-offset-4 hover:text-blood">Contact</a>
            <span class="text-mute"> &mdash; ideas, corrections, or feedback.</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <footer class="mt-24 pt-12 border-t border-ink/10">
      <a href="/" class="btn-primary">Back to the calculator</a>
    </footer>
  </main>

  <SiteFooter />
</Base>
